</title>
<subSubSection id="D3E5572D2CFABDEB3AEB515F7058A1E2" pageId="null" pageNumber="211" type="description">
<paragraph id="3E9649281855A15A44904C30D2FF4F83" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">
Ausdauernd oder 1 
<normalizedToken id="9461354DCE7F0B25E3D546DC2612C005" originalValue="jährig" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">jaehrig</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis id="E48EADB14F1FD9075847B6C1C68B1891" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">
Stengel ohne 
<normalizedToken id="0E03B7D777303E0174CDEAC42C751D7E" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="948BECA75C2FEFDD196CC695BAFFFAC3" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
eine 
<normalizedToken id="467A8C234AEB61D39EB6CD7BDED698E4" originalValue="reichblütige" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">reichbluetige</normalizedToken>
Traube. 
<normalizedToken id="9D008FF5B38FF13419D9D7D5A1DE8086" originalValue="Staubblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Staubblaetter</normalizedToken>
sitzend.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="E4E94A29417FD55177A834E6E49ABEEA" originalValue="Fruchtblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Fruchtblaetter</normalizedToken>
6, 
<emphasis id="88ADA7D6BB1BD8122C17E89F5EF475E7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">
zur 
<normalizedToken id="47F5C1730A9058E99B0B2B77631FC238" originalValue="Blütezeit" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Bluetezeit</normalizedToken>
in der ganzen 
<normalizedToken id="C40CFD17FE43E01D6E6D50871ECD6B2C" originalValue="Länge" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Laenge</normalizedToken>
verwachsen, zur Fruchtzeit trennen sich die 
<normalizedToken id="8BD4A8F6E4809493C4E4BC6DBFFA5F09" originalValue="Früchtblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Fruechtblaetter</normalizedToken>
von unten her
</emphasis>
(nur bei 
<taxonomicName id="BD399EBF236D3A9183ABA5C773FA57B9" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaginaceae" genus="Triglochin" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="null" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritima">
<emphasis id="654732CA537EFE2A1D59EE2CB08E238E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">T. maritima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
alle fruchtbar, bei allen andern Arten 
<emphasis id="03456C1E2FE0303ECEA481089832F632" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">3 fruchtbar</emphasis>
); 
<normalizedToken id="F68E44CFE597494EA9634BBC93ECD614" originalValue="Früchtchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Fruechtchen</normalizedToken>
1samig.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A037C3DE74AF987C56110D86E3EB2E4" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">
Die Gattung 
<emphasis id="034B572970EDC9C395C00E6F5414F1EF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">
<normalizedToken id="774783B353D8D565B105ADBC21C44571" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">umfasst</normalizedToken>
etwa 14 Arten;
</emphasis>
sie ist 
<emphasis id="285F39AC78EF7154510A38AA4B837429" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">
<normalizedToken id="9E9C99DEC3E1286F6F64DFEF81DB4EC3" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">ueber</normalizedToken>
die ganze Erde verbreitet.
</emphasis>
Endemische, 1 
<normalizedToken id="FCB14125A7B75242AA0C32CFEC1070F3" originalValue="jährige" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">jaehrige</normalizedToken>
Arten in Australien. In 
<taxonomicName id="1064FE82CA27ACE40B4D87BB7378943E" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
4 Arten; im Gebiet nur 
<taxonomicName id="3FF59D89886FCF2D6749BB4F242C2ADE" authority="L. Ungewoehnliche" authorityName="L. Ungewoehnliche" class="Liliopsida" family="Scheuchzeriaceae" genus="Scheuchzeria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="null" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis id="A17DC0C70DA8FCBE4092197E18B1B13A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">T. palustris</emphasis>
<authorityName id="7C5FDA09EFD2E1870CB63ADBBF64A4D4" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">L.</authorityName>
<emphasis id="904868A1F60BFEC240B31E5089D157BD" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">
<normalizedToken id="C04DC809BFB91F8BC4A8CDBF3F46E7D7" originalValue="Ungewöhnliche" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Ungewoehnliche</normalizedToken>
polyploide Reihe
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bei der eurasiatisch-amerikanischen Artengruppe von 
<taxonomicName id="2C3203958194FF9A4D4D6A4C3D417981" authority="Zwischen" authorityName="Zwischen" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaginaceae" genus="Triglochin" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="null" pageNumber="211" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maritimum">
<emphasis id="54E355FBF2C86AB5A0F7935DE9917581" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">T. maritimum:</emphasis>
Zwischen
</taxonomicName>
2n = 12 und 144 Chromosomen (24ploid) sind 5 weitere Zahlen der Reihe festgestellt (
<normalizedToken id="A4A735EDD1BC7FEEFD35B9807B43F231" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="969E131C1D216FBEA95214CD08BCA050" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="211">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1958a 1958b).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
